# Tooltip Component Rule

The [Tooltip.vue](mdc:src/components/ui/Tooltip.vue) component follows shadcn-vue conventions:

- Single File Component (SFC) in `src/components/ui`.
- Used for displaying contextual information on hover or focus.
- Accepts `enabled`, `title`, `shortcut`, and `tippyOptions` props.
- Uses [vue-tippy](mdc:https:/kabbouchi.github.io/vue-tippy) for tooltip rendering and positioning.
- Supports keyboard shortcut display with custom rendering for Mac/Windows keys.
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling and utility classes.

For tooltip best practices, see the [shadcn-vue Tooltip documentation](mdc:https:/www.shadcn-vue.com/docs/components/tooltip) as a reference.





